'''现代货币理论'''（缩写'''MMT'''）是一种[[非主流經濟學|非主流]]<ref name="Heterodox Views of Money and Modern Monetary Theory (MMT): Phil Armstrong">{{Cite web|url=https://moslereconomics.com/wp-content/uploads/2007/12/Money-and-MMT.pdf|title=Heterodox Views of Money and Modern Monetary Theory (MMT)|accessdate=2020-06-28|archive-date=2016-06-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160603145524/http://moslereconomics.com/wp-content/uploads/2007/12/Money-and-MMT.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>[[宏观经济学|宏观经济学]]理论，认为现代货币体系实际上是一种政府信用货币体系。<ref>Warren Mosler, [http://www00.unibg.it/dati/corsi/910003/64338-Warren%20Mosler%20Bergamo%20paper%20March%2010.pdf ME/MMT: The Currency as a Public Monopoly] {{Wayback|url=http://www00.unibg.it/dati/corsi/910003/64338-Warren%20Mosler%20Bergamo%20paper%20March%2010.pdf |date=20200228132918 }}</ref>
现代货币理论即[[主權國家|主權國家]]的货币並不与任何商品和其他外币挂钩，只与未来[[税收|税收]]與[[公债|公债]]相对应。<ref>[https://papers.ssrn.com/sol3/papers.cfm?abstract_id=3569416 Modern Modern Monetary Theory (MMT): A General Introduction.] {{Wayback|url=https://papers.ssrn.com/sol3/papers.cfm?abstract_id=3569416 |date=20200427164420 }} ''Macroeconomics: Monetary & Fiscal Policies eJournal.'' Social Science Research Network (SSRN). Accessed 14 June 2020.</ref>因為主权货币具有[[无限法偿|无限法偿]]性質，没有名义预算约束，只存在[[通貨膨脹|通貨膨脹]]的实际约束。<ref name="MMTreply">Éric Tymoigne and L. Randall Wray, [http://www.levyinstitute.org/pubs/wp_778.pdf "Modern Money Theory 101: A Reply to Critics,"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.levyinstitute.org/pubs/wp_778.pdf |date=20200320010440 }} Levy Economics Institute of Bard College, Working Paper No. 778 (November 2013).</ref>主张[[功能性财政|功能性财政]]，即应由[[財政部|財政部]]代替[[中央銀行|中央銀行]]承担实现消滅[[失業率|失業率]]和避免過度的[[通貨膨脹|通貨膨脹]]的职能。<ref name=planetmoney>{{cite news |last=Goldmark |first=Alex |date=September 26, 2018 |title=Episode 866: Modern Monetary Theory |url=https://www.npr.org/sections/money/2018/09/26/651948323/episode-866-modern-monetary-theory |work=NPR |location=Washington DC |access-date=September 26, 2019 |archive-date=2020-07-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200711161844/https://www.npr.org/sections/money/2018/09/26/651948323/episode-866-modern-monetary-theory |dead-url=no }}</ref>

现代货币理论認為，货币的唯一價值就是公家賦予的繳稅功能，政府可以一直發行貨幣來活絡市場，唯一制约超发货币的因素就是通货膨胀；但公家可以通过課税，来收取民間擁有的货币，以避免通货膨胀。<ref name=nytimes>{{cite news |last=Cohen |first=Patricia |date=April 5, 2019 |title=Modern Monetary Theory Finds an Embrace in an Unexpected Place: Wall Street |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/04/05/business/economy/mmt-wall-street.html |work=[[New_York_Times|New York Times]] |location=New York |access-date=April 5, 2019 |archive-date=2020-07-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200708202932/https://www.nytimes.com/2019/04/05/business/economy/mmt-wall-street.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>

[[1990年代|1990年代]]中期以后，[[日本|日本]]是实践了现代货币理论的先行国家：<ref name="Wray2015">{{cite book | last=Wray | first=L. Randall | title=Modern Money Theory: A Primer on Macroeconomics for Sovereign Monetary Systems | publisher=Palgrave Macmillan | location=Houndmills, Basingstoke, Hampshire New York, NY | year=2015 | isbn=978-1-137-53990-8 | pages=137–141, 199–206}}</ref>大量發行货币，但是没有[[惡性通货膨胀|惡性通货膨胀]]；不追求预算與支出平衡，通过零利率甚至负利率，以保障[[国债|国债]]利息支出不爆炸；課徵[[消费税|消费税]]以保障基本[[社会福利|社会福利]]与社会基础设施更新。

